trend_summary: Across the time series, forested terrain is progressively replaced by curvilinear housing estates and an enlarging industrial/commercial cluster to the east. Highways and collectors are extended, enabling west-ward infill. Though a few cleared sites later greened over, net tree cover falls and the built footprint nearly doubles, yielding medium-density suburbia.
notable_changes: Curvy residential subdivisions spread north-west and south-west, occupying former forest.
Eastern industrial/commercial zone grows southward with larger rooftops and parking.
New/expanded arterial road bisects the area, linking developments and spurring infill.
Overall vegetation cover declines; isolated re-greening seen on a few cleared lots.
Scattered infill housing increases density inside earlier neighbourhood envelopes.
